      <div class="hero">
        <section class="left">
          <div class="title">
            <h1>Verifiable Evidence in 5 seconds</h1>
            <p><strong>NOT a prediction model.</strong> EV424 verifies byte-level integrity via SHA-256.<br/>Same input → same output. PASS is earned. FAIL is preserved.</p>

            <div class="chips" aria-label="Key principles">
              <span class="chip">SHA-256 gate</span>
              <span class="chip">exposure-min</span>
              <span class="chip">external assets: 0</span>
              <span class="chip">manual deploy</span>
            </div>

            <div class="subline">
              Domain-agnostic rail (FACT): if it produces <strong>files/logs/records</strong>, EV424 can seal and re-verify bytes.
              What we publish is only <strong>public_data</strong> + verifiable SHA-256 proofs. No secrets. No PII. No internal paths.
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="panel" id="public" aria-label="Verify (FACT)">
            <h2>Verify (FACT)</h2>
            <pre class="mono"><code>1) Download public_data/toc.json and public_data/toc.json.sha256
2) Run: sha256sum -c toc.json.sha256
3) Expect: toc.json: OK</code></pre>
            <p class="hint">“OK” means the bytes match the published SHA-256. (Integrity verification only)</p>
          </div>

          <div class="cta" role="group" aria-label="Primary actions">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/public_data/toc.json">Open public_data</a>
            <a class="btn" href="/public_data/toc.json.sha256">Get sha256 proof</a>
            <a class="btn" href="#how">How verification works</a>
          </div>

          <div class="links" aria-label="Public data entries">
            <a class="link" href="/public_data/toc.json">
