      <div class="sections">
        <div class="grid" id="how">
          <div class="card">
            <strong>1) Preflight Gate</strong>
            Gate confirms: external assets = 0, exposure-min, deploy-eligible structure.
            <div class="pill">preflight → PASS/FAIL</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <strong>2) Direct Deploy</strong>
            Manual deployment only (wrangler). A deploy is an event recorded by you.
            <div class="pill">wrangler deploy → event</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <strong>3) Hash Closure</strong>
            Closure is proven only when remote bytes match local bytes via SHA-256.
            <div class="pill">sha256(remote) == sha256(local)</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid" id="scope">
          <div class="card">
            <strong>Domain-Agnostic Rail (FACT)</strong>
            EV424 does not judge meaning. It verifies integrity at the byte level (SHA-256).
            <div class="pill">bytes → hash → re-verify</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <strong>Cross-Domain Fit (FACT)</strong>
            Works wherever outputs exist as files/logs/records (numbers or structured text).
            <div class="pill">logs/files/records</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <strong>Evidence Location (FACT)</strong>
            Verifiable examples are published as <span class="mono">/public_data</span> + <span class="mono">.sha256</span> proofs.
            <div class="pill">public_data + sha256</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="grid" id="threat">
          <div class="card">
            <strong>Threat: External Asset Drift</strong>
            Missing assets can still return <em>200 text/html</em> and fake success. EV424 avoids this by assets=0.
            <div class="pill">assets=0</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <strong>Threat: Content-Type Mismatch</strong>
            If expected types are returned as html, the gate should record FAIL to prevent silent drift.
            <div class="pill">mismatch → FAIL</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <strong>Preserve FAIL Evidence</strong>
            FAIL is not discarded; it should be quarantined/preserved to avoid repeating the same class of mistakes.
            <div class="pill">FAIL preserved</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="footer">
        <span>EV424 verifies integrity (byte-level), not truth of contents.</span>
        <span>Accuracy(4)=Truth(2)=Life(4)</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
